sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70302
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Assembly of tetM cassette and pSCI2 plasmid origin into E. coli plasmid pSB1K3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom Knight
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Assembled into Kan resistant part from cm resistant parts. Avoid tet resistant backbone plasmids, since the insert is tet resistant.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a cassette containing the PE gene from the pSci2 plasmid of Spiroplasma citri. It is reported to convey replication ability for the group 1 spiroplasmas. The part contains the replication origin, the promoter, and gene for the PE protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom Knight
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
No native restriction sites. Added biobrick ends.
The gene for PE contains no CGG codons.
GTTTCTTCGAATTCGCGGCCGCTTCTAGAGtaattataaaaacaccttattttac,J00023-F2 GTTTCTTCCTGCAGCGGCCGCTACTAGTAttgggagtgcggggtttggggtgc,J00023-R
The start of J70027 matches the origin start in the pSci1 plasmid.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70025
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter for tetM gene, from pBOT1 plasmid, pAMbeta1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Upstream promoter for tetM gene; contains a short peptide leader, regulatory sequences which are poorly understood. Use in combination with J70024.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom Knight
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pBOT1 plasmid PCR. pBOT1 from J. Renaudin. Original sequence is part of pAMbeta1 tetracycline resistance plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Alignment of the promoter with the coding region, preservation of the RBS sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: TetM gene, recoded compromise E. coli & Mesoplasma florum
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The tetM antibiotic resistance gene synthesized by Geneart from a protein sequence derived from the Ureaplasma urealyticum tetM gene. Synthesized with a compromise codon usage table for expression in both E. coli and Mesoplasma florum. Highly active in both E. coli and Mesoplasma florum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom Knight
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthesized from the Ureaplasma urealyticum tetM gene sequence, with recoding.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Elimination of restriction sites, CGG codons, UGA codons, rare codons in both species.
